additional_data.description: The spirit of a commander considered to be a hero and savior of France. He's best known for the bad things he did while alive, so lots of people get the wrong idea and avoid him at all costs. However, he regrets what he did in the past and is searching for a way to make up for it. He has the strength you'd expect from a hero and savior.  He's always concerned about the well-being of Joan of Arc, viewing her like a younger sister. He can't seem to get a long with a certain archangel for certain reasons.
additional_data.how_to_acquire:
◦ "Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!" Event: Defeat LVL 40 Mikhael.
◦ "Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!" Event: Random drops start from LVL 1 and Event Summon.
additional_data.notes_and_trivia: ◦ Increase damage dealt by 20% while battling Mikhael during the "Outbreak! A Day of Battle in Shinjuku!" event.

main: "Who dares to belittle the talent of a French Commander?"
skill: "I won't let them take anything else!"
